<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,604,2071]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
Differs from the most similar species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hooker" authorityYear="1892" box="[553,657,604,630]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Tupistra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="clarkei">
<emphasis box="[553,657,604,630]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">T. clarkei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by its wider leaves, upright or ascending spike, smaller flowers, perianth dark purple on both sides, laterally strongly revolute perianth lobes, and stamens adnate to the subbasal portion of the lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
